                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;I don&apos;t know about C++ but the C standard says that a conversion of an int to a char is either implementation defined or even well defined (depending on the actual values and signedness of types). See C99 ยง6.3.1.3 (unchanged in C11).&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/104790/nikolai-ruhe&quot; title=&quot;80,654 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Nikolai Ruhe&lt;/a&gt;
